## Priority Quick Reference

| Priority | Meaning | Analysis required |
|----------|---------|-------------------|
| P0 | Critical differentiator — market gap | Architect + Staff + PO sign-off |
| P1 | Competitive parity — leaders have it | Architect + Staff |
| P2 | Strategic advantage — unique to Lyx | Staff review minimum |
| P3 | Nice to have | Backlog entry sufficient |

## When Acting as Agent

- If the user requests a new feature, first check if it exists in `docs/backlog.md`
- If not, create a backlog entry with competitive justification before implementing
- For P0/P1 items, always document the Architect and Staff analysis in `docs/workplan.md`
- **After implementing, ALWAYS run QA regression before committing**
- After QA passes, update backlog status and documentation
- If a bug is found post-commit, add it to the QA skill's "Known Bug Patterns" so it never happens again
